Vegan Mushroom Stroganoff.all_ingredients: Mushrooms, Onion, Garlic, Vegetable Broth, Coconut Milk, Soy Sauce, Dijon Mustard, Paprika, Cornstarch, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper, Parsley
Vegan Mushroom Stroganoff.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add minced garlic and cook for another 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add sliced mushrooms to the skillet and cook until they release their juices and start to brown, about 8-10 minutes.
In a small bowl, whisk together vegetable broth, coconut milk, soy sauce, Dijon mustard, paprika, and cornstarch until smooth.
Pour the mixture into the skillet with the mushrooms. Stir well to combine.
Simmer the stroganoff for 5-7 minutes until the sauce thickens.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve hot over cooked pasta, rice, or mashed potatoes, garnished with chopped parsley.

Moroccan Carrot Soup.all_ingredients: Carrots, Onion, Garlic Clove, Cumin, Coriander, Olive Oil, Garam Masala, Lemon Juice
Moroccan Carrot Soup.instructions:
Step 1
Preheat oven to 180° C.
Step 2
Combine carrots, onion, garlic, cumin seeds, coriander seeds, salt and olive oil in a bowl and mix well. Transfer on a baking tray.
Step 3
Put the baking tray in preheated oven and roast for 10-12 minutes or till carrots soften. Remove from heat and cool.
Step 4
Grind the baked carrot mixture along with some water to make a smooth paste and strain in a bowl.
Step 5
Heat the carrot mixture in a non-stick pan. Add two cups of water and bring to a boil. Add garam masala powder and mix. Add salt and mix well.
Step 6
Remove from heat, add lemon juice and mix well.
Step 7
Serve hot.

Vegan Falafel Wraps.all_ingredients: Chickpeas, Onion, Garlic, Parsley, Cumin, Coriander, Baking Powder, Flour, Salt, Black Pepper, Olive Oil, Wraps, Lettuce, Tomatoes, Cucumber, Tahini Sauce
Vegan Falafel Wraps.instructions:
Step 1
In a food processor, combine chickpeas, chopped onion, minced garlic, parsley, cumin, coriander, baking powder, flour, salt, and black pepper.
Step 2
Pulse until the mixture is coarsely ground but not pureed.
Step 3
Form the mixture into small balls or patties and flatten slightly.
Step 4
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Step 5
Cook the falafel until browned and crispy on both sides, about 4 minutes per side.
Step 6
Serve the falafel in wraps with lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, and tahini sauce.

Vegan Chocolate Avocado Mousse.all_ingredients: Avocado, Cocoa Powder, Maple Syrup, Vanilla Extract
Vegan Chocolate Avocado Mousse.instructions:
Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides as needed.
Taste and adjust sweetness if needed by adding more maple syrup.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving to allow the mousse to set.
Serve chilled, topped with your favorite fruits or nuts if desired.

Vegan Lentil Soup.all_ingredients: Lentils, Onion, Carrots, Celery, Garlic, Vegetable Broth, Cumin, Paprika, Bay Leaf, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper, Parsley
Vegan Lentil Soup.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add diced onions, carrots, and celery. Cook until vegetables are softened, about 5-7 minutes.
Add minced garlic, cumin, paprika, and bay leaf. Cook for another 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add dried lentils and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until lentils are tender, about 20-25 minutes.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley.

Vegan Pad Thai.all_ingredients: Rice Noodles, Tofu, Carrots, Bell Peppers, Bean Sprouts, Green Onions, Garlic, Peanuts, Lime, Soy Sauce, Rice Vinegar, Maple Syrup, Sriracha, Olive Oil
Vegan Pad Thai.instructions:
Cook rice noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced tofu and cook until golden brown and crispy on all sides, about 8-10 minutes. Remove tofu from skillet and set aside.
In the same skillet, add minced garlic and cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add sliced carrots and bell peppers to the skillet. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 5-7 minutes.
Add cooked rice noodles, bean sprouts, green onions, and cooked tofu to the skillet. Stir well to combine.
In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, rice vinegar, maple syrup, and sriracha. Pour the sauce over the noodles and tofu. Stir fry for another 2-3 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped peanuts and lime wedges.

Vegan Chickpea Curry.all_ingredients: Chickpeas, Onion, Garlic, Ginger, Bell Pepper, Coconut Milk, Tomato Paste, Curry Powder, Turmeric, Cumin, Cayenne Pepper, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper, Cilantro
Vegan Chickpea Curry.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced onions, minced garlic, and grated ginger. Cook until onions are softened, about 5 minutes.
Add diced bell peppers to the skillet. Cook for another 3-4 minutes until peppers are tender.
Add tomato paste, curry powder, turmeric, cumin, and cayenne pepper to the skillet. Stir well to combine.
Pour in coconut milk and drained chickpeas. Bring to a simmer and cook for 10-15 minutes until flavors are well combined.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro.

Vegan Sushi Rolls.all_ingredients: Sushi Rice, Nori Sheets, Avocado, Cucumber, Carrots, Bell Pepper, Tofu, Soy Sauce, Rice Vinegar, Maple Syrup, Wasabi, Pickled Ginger
Vegan Sushi Rolls.instructions:
Cook sushi rice according to package instructions. Season with rice vinegar and maple syrup.
Place a nori sheet on a bamboo sushi mat. Spread a thin layer of sushi rice evenly over the nori sheet.
Arrange sliced avocado, cucumber, carrots, bell pepper, and tofu strips in the center of the rice.
Roll the sushi tightly using the bamboo mat. Seal the edge of the nori sheet with a little water.
Slice the sushi roll into bite-sized pieces using a sharp knife.
Serve with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger.

Vegan Buddha Bowl.all_ingredients: Quinoa, Chickpeas, Sweet Potato, Kale, Avocado, Cherry Tomatoes, Red Cabbage, Tahini Sauce, Lemon Juice, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper
Vegan Buddha Bowl.instructions:
Cook quinoa according to package instructions. Set aside.
Roast sweet potato cubes in the oven at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 minutes until tender.
Massage kale leaves with olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.
Assemble buddha bowls with cooked quinoa, roasted sweet potatoes, massaged kale, chickpeas, sliced avocado, halved cherry tomatoes, and shredded red cabbage.
Drizzle with tahini sauce.
Serve immediately.

Vegan Black Bean Tacos.all_ingredients: Black Beans, Onion, Garlic, Bell Pepper, Chili Powder, Cumin, Paprika, Cayenne Pepper, Lime, Tortillas, Avocado, Cilantro, Salsa
Vegan Black Bean Tacos.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced onions and minced garlic. Cook until onions are softened, about 5 minutes.
Add diced bell peppers to the skillet. Cook for another 3-4 minutes until peppers are tender.
Add black beans, chili powder, cumin, paprika, and cayenne pepper to the skillet. Stir well to combine.
Squeeze lime juice over the black bean mixture. Cook for another 2-3 minutes.
Warm tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave.
Assemble tacos with black bean mixture, sliced avocado, and chopped cilantro.
Serve with salsa on the side.

Vegan Lentil Shepherd's Pie.all_ingredients: Lentils, Onion, Carrots, Celery, Garlic, Tomato Paste, Vegetable Broth, Cornstarch, Soy Sauce, Thyme, Rosemary, Mashed Potatoes, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper
Vegan Lentil Shepherd's Pie.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced onions, carrots, and celery. Cook until vegetables are softened, about 5-7 minutes.
Add minced garlic and cook for another 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add tomato paste, vegetable broth, lentils, cornstarch, soy sauce, thyme, and rosemary to the skillet. Stir well to combine.
Simmer the mixture for 20-25 minutes until lentils are tender and the sauce has thickened.
Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
Transfer the lentil mixture to a baking dish. Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes until the mashed potatoes are golden brown.
Serve hot.

Vegan Thai Green Curry.all_ingredients: Coconut Milk, Thai Green Curry Paste, Tofu, Bell Pepper, Zucchini, Carrots, Bamboo Shoots, Thai Basil, Lime Leaves, Soy Sauce, Maple Syrup, Olive Oil, Rice
Vegan Thai Green Curry.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced tofu and cook until golden brown and crispy on all sides, about 8-10 minutes. Remove tofu from skillet and set aside.
In the same skillet, add sliced bell peppers, zucchini, carrots, and bamboo shoots. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 5-7 minutes.
Add Thai green curry paste to the skillet. Stir well to coat the vegetables.
Pour in coconut milk and soy sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5-7 minutes.
Add cooked tofu, Thai basil, and lime leaves to the skillet. Stir well to combine.
Season with maple syrup to taste.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

Vegan Mediterranean Couscous Salad.all_ingredients: Couscous, Cherry Tomatoes, Cucumber, Red Onion, Kalamata Olives, Fresh Parsley, Fresh Mint, Lemon Juice, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper
Vegan Mediterranean Couscous Salad.instructions:
Cook couscous according to package instructions. Fluff with a fork and let cool.
In a large bowl, combine cooked couscous, halved cherry tomatoes, diced cucumber, thinly sliced red onion, pitted and halved kalamata olives, chopped fresh parsley, and chopped fresh mint.
Drizzle olive oil and lemon juice over the salad. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Toss gently to combine.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

Vegan Sweet Potato and Black Bean Chili.all_ingredients: Sweet Potato, Black Beans, Onion, Bell Pepper, Garlic, Diced Tomatoes, Vegetable Broth, Chili Powder, Cumin, Paprika, Cayenne Pepper, Olive Oil, Salt, Black Pepper, Avocado, Cilantro
Vegan Sweet Potato and Black Bean Chili.instructions:
Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add diced onions, bell peppers, and minced garlic. Cook until onions are softened, about 5 minutes.
Add diced sweet potatoes, black beans, diced tomatoes, vegetable broth, chili powder, cumin, paprika, and cayenne pepper to the pot. Stir well to combine.
Bring the chili to a simmer and cook for 20-25 minutes until sweet potatoes are tender.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve hot, garnished with sliced avocado and chopped cilantro.

Vegan Eggplant Parmesan.all_ingredients: Eggplant, Flour, Almond Milk, Breadcrumbs, Nutritional Yeast, Italian Seasoning, Garlic Powder, Marinara Sauce, Vegan Cheese, Fresh Basil
Vegan Eggplant Parmesan.instructions:
Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Slice the eggplant into ½ inch rounds.
In one bowl, mix flour and almond milk. In another bowl, mix breadcrumbs, nutritional yeast, Italian seasoning, and garlic powder.
Dip each eggplant slice into the flour mixture, then the breadcrumb mixture, ensuring they're evenly coated.
Place the coated eggplant slices on the prepared baking sheet and bake for 20-25 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden brown.
Spread marinara sauce on each eggplant slice and sprinkle with vegan cheese.
Return to the oven and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes, until the cheese is melted and bubbly.
Garnish with fresh basil before serving.
